  </div>

  <div style="background:#001b16;padding:3rem 4rem;text-align:center;border-top:1px solid rgba(37,159,138,0.15);border-bottom:1px solid rgba(37,159,138,0.15);">
    <span style="font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#259f8a;display:block;margin-bottom:1.5rem;">The Cigar Band</span>
    <img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="The Third Rule cigar band" style="max-width:780px;width:100%;box-shadow:0 4px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);display:block;margin:0 auto;">
    <p style="font-family:var(--font-sans);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:0.15em;text-transform:uppercase;color:rgba(224,254,248,0.35);margin-top:1.25rem;">Designed by Jennifer Hogan · Exclusive to The Tobacco Center · Williamsport, PA</p>
  </div>

  <div class="tr-story">
    <svg class="leaf" style="right:-4%;top:8%;width:32%;opacity:0.09;" viewBox="0 0 500 640" fill="none"><path d="M250 30 C165 65 55 175 45 310 C35 445 115 570 240 580 C365 590 455 470 455 335 C455 200 355 55 250 30Z" fill="#4dbf8a"/><path d="M250 30 L250 580" stroke="#4dbf8a" stroke-width="4"/><path d="M120 155 C165 200 210 210 250 192" stroke="#4dbf8a" stroke-width="2.5"/><path d="M75 275 C135 305 195 312 250 290" stroke="#4dbf8a" stroke-width="2.5"/><ellipse cx="130" cy="185" rx="35" ry="17" fill="none" stroke="#4dbf8a" stroke-width="1.8"/></svg>
    <div style="position:relative;z-index:1;">
      <span class="eyebrow">The Story Behind the Cigar</span>
      <h2>Discipline, Standards, and a <em>Serious Smoke.</em></h2>
      <p>The Third Rule isn't a house cigar that exists to fill a shelf. It's the result of a real collaboration between The Tobacco Center's owner and Navy Veteran Gray Hogan and one of the most respected blenders in the world.</p>
      <p>Gray brought a precise vision: a cigar that reflected the discipline and standards of his Navy background — bold enough to stand out, balanced enough to reward the patient smoker. He took that vision to Karen Berger at her factory in Estelí, Nicaragua, and together they built something worth talking about.</p>
      <p>The cigar is headlined by a rare AJ Fernandez Cameroon wrapper, known for its distinctive spice and subtle sweetness. Beneath that sits a rich Nicaraguan Oscuro binder and a potent double ligero filler from the legendary growing region of Estelí. This cigar packs a serious punch. It's not for the timid, and it's not trying to be.</p>
      <div class="tr-quote">
        "Developing 'The Third Rule' was an exercise in precision. I wanted a cigar that reflected the discipline and standards of my Navy background while offering a profile that truly stands out in a humidor. Having Karen Berger bring those ideas to life at her factory was an incredible experience."
        <cite>— Gray Hogan, Owner &amp; Navy Veteran, The Tobacco Center</cite>
      </div>
      <p>Named after The Tobacco Center's 3rd Lounge Rule — the heart of what makes this place what it is — The Third Rule is a Tobacco Center exclusive. It will not be found in online catalogs or other retailers. You have to come in. We wouldn't have it any other way.</p>
      <p><strong>Available in singles and bundles starting April 24th.</strong></p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="tr-sidebar-card">
        <h4>Product Specifications</h4>
        <table class="spec-table">
          <tr><td>Name</td><td>The Third Rule</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Blender</td><td>Karen Berger</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Wrapper</td><td>AJ Fernandez Cameroon</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Binder</td><td>Nicaraguan Oscuro</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Filler</td><td>Double Ligero, Estelí, Nicaragua</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Formats</td><td>Singles &amp; Bundles</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Availability</td><td>Exclusive — The Tobacco Center only</td></tr>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="tr-sidebar-card">
        <h4>About Karen Berger</h4>
        <p>Known as the "Queen of Cigars," Karen Berger is a world-renowned blender and the driving force behind K. by Karen Berger. Based in Estelí, Nicaragua, she is one of the few women leading a major cigar operation — celebrated for her mastery of traditional Nicaraguan tobacco.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="tr-sidebar-card">
        <h4>Exclusively Here</h4>
        <p>The Third Rule will not be found in online catalogs or at other retailers. It is available only at The Tobacco Center, 21 W Church St, Williamsport, PA.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

